{
  "title": "Quantum computers tackle unexplored particle physics",
  "url": "https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-025-01797-3",
  "content": "Subatomic particles such as quarks can pair up when linked by â€˜stringsâ€™ of force fields â€” and release energy when the strings are pulled to the point of breaking. Two teams of physicists have now used quantum computers to mimic this phenomenon and watch it unfold in real time.\n\nThe results, described in two _Nature_ papers on 4 June1,2, are the latest in a series of breakthroughs towards using quantum computers for simulations that are beyond the ability of any ordinary computers."
